olive oil
1 packet Peeled Pumpkin Pieces
1 unit parsnip
½ unit onion
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
1 tsp plain flour
1 packet chicken thigh
1 packet flaked almonds
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise

Preheat the oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Slice the peeled pumpkin into 1cm wedges. Cut the parsnip (unpeeled) into 1cm chunks. Slice the red onion (see ingredients) into 2cm wedges.
TIP: Cut the veggies to size so they cook in time.

Spread the veggies over two oven trays lined with baking paper. Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat and spread in a single layer. Roast until golden and tender, 25-30 minutes.

While the veggies are roasting, combine the Aussie spice blend, plain flour and a drizzle of olive oil in a large bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then add the chicken thigh and toss to coat. When the veggies have 20 minutes cook time remaining, move the veggies to one side of an oven tray and add the chicken. Return the tray to the oven and bake until cooked through.
TIP: The chicken is cooked through when it's no longer pink inside.

While the chicken is baking, heat a medium frying pan over a medium-high heat. Add the flaked almonds and toast, tossing, until golden, 2-3 minutes. Set aside.

When the chicken and veggies are done, add the baby spinach leaves to the oven tray and gently toss to combine.

Slice the chicken. Divide the roasted veggies between plates and top with the golden-spiced chicken. Serve with the dill & parsley mayonnaise and garnish with the toasted almonds.